definitions: To arrive at a place, especially a destination.
To be accepted or admitted into a place, group, or institution.
To submit or deliver something by a deadline.
To enter a vehicle, building, or enclosed space.
To succeed in doing something, often with difficulty.
examples: What time did you get in last night?
She was so happy to get in to her dream university.
Make sure to get in your application before Friday.
We managed to get in a quick workout before dinner.
